genresAdvancedInfo.name: hungarian techno
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Hungarian techno is a high-energy, electronic dance music genre that emerged in the 1990s. It is characterized by its repetitive beats, synthesized sounds and use of technology to create a futuristic sound. Hungarian techno DJs and producers are known for their innovative approach to music, often incorporating elements of other genres such as house, trance and ambient music into their sets.
